The paper deals with the abstract categorical setting of double-pushout (DPO) rewriting, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and mathematics. The paper also mentions the application of the concept to define and compute the evolution of statistical moments of observables in stochastic DPO rewriting systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
